{"schema_version":"v1","message_id":"202605301054080_blocker","session_id":"ses_18787d50affe3zPIkFmfAd8Tyg","sender":"lane-owner","recipient":"orchestrator","kind":"blocker","wave":null,"subject":"Lane AH-002 — failure propagation dedup blocked by AH-001","body":"{\"lane_id\":\"AH-002\",\"blocked_at\":\"execution\",\"finding\":\"Test 2 (compute failure propagation) reveals the race condition AH-001 is fixing. When compute fails via Effect.die, the inflight dedup doesn't work — all 10 concurrently waiting fibers independently run compute instead of deduping. The success case (Test 1) passes because synchronous compute completes before other fibers can race. Root cause: the Deferred in cache.ts has error channel 'never' but is completed with failure exits via 'as any' cast, which causes Deferred.await to produce a defect instead of propagating the failure.\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"keep-test-expecting-correct-behavior\",\"description\":\"Keep test as-is expecting computeCount=1 (correct post-fix behavior). Test will fail now but pass after AH-001 lands. ~0 lines\",\"effort\":\"0 lines\"},{\"id\":\"adjust-test-for-current-broken-state\",\"description\":\"Adjust test to accept computeCount=10 for now, then revert after AH-001 fix. ~10 lines\",\"effort\":\"~10 lines\"}],\"recommended\":\"keep-test-expecting-correct-behavior\",\"attempted\":[\"Using Effect.die for compute error\",\"Using Ref-based counter for thread-safe counting\",\"Verified Test 1 (success) passes correctly with count=1\"]}","sent_at":"2026-05-30T10:54:08.063Z"}
