{"schema_version":"v1","message_id":"202605301153168_handoff","session_id":"ses_18748c5b1ffe6av6JnMTkQ2DSK","sender":"lane-owner","recipient":"orchestrator","kind":"handoff","wave":null,"subject":"Lane RL-005 complete — Plugin Security Manifest + Trust Model","body":"{\n  \"lane_id\": \"RL-005\",\n  \"status\": \"completed\",\n  \"waves_completed\": [\"learning\", \"plan\", \"review\", \"execution\", \"validation\"],\n  \"repair_cycles\": 0,\n  \"claims_verified\": 3,\n  \"files_created\": [\"docs/json/opencode/audits/plugin-security-manifest-audit.v1.json\"],\n  \"files_modified\": [],\n  \"verification\": {\n    \"typecheck\": \"pass\",\n    \"tests\": \"pass\"\n  },\n  \"blockers\": [],\n  \"lessons\": [\n    \"The plugin API grants full process access by design; any trust model must be retrofitted as a capability manifest layer without breaking existing first-party auth plugins.\"\n  ],\n  \"recommendation\": \"merge\",\n  \"findings_artifact\": \"docs/json/opencode/audits/plugin-security-manifest-audit.v1.json\",\n  \"summary\": {\n    \"architecture\": \"Mapped dual plugin system (server/CLI + desktop Electron). Server side uses Effect service with PluginLoader pipeline (resolve→load→applyPlugin→hooks). Desktop side uses DesktopPluginLoader with dynamic import in renderer process. Both share @opencode-ai/plugin SDK with 21+ lifecycle hooks, unrestricted tool registration, and zero sandboxing.\",\n    \"security_audit\": \"Answered 11 adversarial questions: 5 CRITICAL (file read, prompt exfiltration, secrets access, config mutation, prompt injection), 4 HIGH (tool impersonation, UI thread locking, lifecycle bypass, fake tool registration), 1 MODERATE (event spam DOS), 1 LOW (persistence after uninstall). Root cause: hooks interface designed for trusted first-party auth providers, no adversarial model.\",\n    \"capability_model\": \"Designed a 14-capability manifest schema (filesystem.read/write, network.request/server, mcp.access, tool.register/modify, event.subscribe, secrets.read, ui.slot, background.execution, autostart, shell.env, session.hooks). Each capability has scope restrictions (path globs, URL patterns, hook allowlists), display text, and risk level. Schema at rig.opencode.plugin_capability.v1.\",\n    \"ui_display\": \"Designed card-based display with capability badges (7 categories), human-readable sentence format ('This plugin can read files in your project and send network requests'), detail expansion panel, risk indicators (colored borders), and per-capability toggles.\",\n    \"implementation_priorities\": \"9 recommendations: P1 (manifest parsing, hook gating, tool namespace), P2 (secrets scoping, desktop sandboxing, tool.modify gate), P3 (permission prompts, rate limiting, install-time validation).\"\n  },\n  \"out_of_scope_findings_recorded\": [\n    \"No security boundary tests exist for the plugin system\",\n    \"PluginTransport type missing from SDK export; preload IPC transport unwired\"\n  ]\n}","sent_at":"2026-05-30T11:53:16.879Z"}
{"schema_version":"v1","message_id":"202605301153312_handoff","session_id":"ses_18748d10cffenCGpohMcaJapaL","sender":"lane-owner","recipient":"orchestrator","kind":"handoff","wave":null,"subject":"Lane RL-004 complete — Secrets Handling Policy Audit","body":"{\n  \"lane_id\": \"RL-004\",\n  \"status\": \"completed\",\n  \"waves_completed\": [\"learning\", \"plan\", \"review\", \"execution\", \"validation\"],\n  \"repair_cycles\": 0,\n  \"claims_verified\": 6,\n  \"files_created\": [\n    \"docs/json/opencode/secrets/rl-004-findings.v1.json\",\n    \"docs/json/opencode/plans/rl-004-secrets-policy.v1.json\"\n  ],\n  \"files_modified\": [],\n  \"verification\": {\n    \"artifact_validated\": \"pass\"\n  },\n  \"blockers\": [],\n  \"findings_summary\": {\n    \"existing_redaction_mechanisms\": 8,\n    \"critical_security_gaps\": 5,\n    \"high_risk_secret_sites\": 13,\n    \"critical_risk_sites\": 2,\n    \"immediate_active_leak_fixes\": 2\n  },\n  \"top_findings\": [\n    \"sanitizedProcessEnv in packages/core/src/util/opencode-process.ts is a NO-OP — named 'sanitized' but passes ALL env vars unchanged to subprocesses\",\n    \"createSidecarEnv in packages/desktop/src/main/server.ts:230 passes ALL env vars including OPENCODE_SERVER_PASSWORD to the sidecar process without filtering\",\n    \"Enterprise storage (packages/enterprise/src/core/storage.ts:67-83) reads AWS access keys/secret keys with non-null assertions — no validation, crash risk\",\n    \"Multiple credential injection sites write secrets into process.env (AWS_BEARER_TOKEN_BEDROCK, AICORE_SERVICE_KEY, OPENCODE_CONSOLE_TOKEN)\",\n    \"No ENV_BLOCKLIST, no file-read security, no bash command security, no general-purpose output scrubber exists anywhere in the codebase\"\n  ],\n  \"critical_gaps\": [\n    \"GAP-A: sanitizedProcessEnv is a no-op (subprocess env passes ALL secrets)\",\n    \"GAP-B: No file-read security (no binary detection, safe path, or sensitive file blocking)\",\n    \"GAP-C: No bash command security (no rerouting, no dangerous pattern detection)\",\n    \"GAP-D: No general-purpose output scrubber (tool output, agent messages, event payloads unprotected)\",\n    \"GAP-E: No central ENV_BLOCKLIST utility exists\"\n  ],\n  \"policy_layers_proposed\": [\n    \"Layer 1: Env-aware secret classifier (P0)\",\n    \"Layer 2: ENV_BLOCKLIST for subprocesses (P0)\",\n    \"Layer 3: Output sanitizer pipeline (P1)\",\n    \"Layer 4: File I/O protection (P1)\",\n    \"Layer 5: Credential lifecycle management (P2)\"\n  ],\n  \"lessons\": [\n    \"No general-purpose secrets redaction exists in this codebase — always audit before assuming\",\n    \"Multiple sites write credentials into process.env as an anti-pattern — use SDK constructors instead\",\n    \"AGENTS.md describes Rig Relay security mechanisms that do NOT exist in this repo\"\n  ],\n  \"recommendation\": \"merge\",\n  \"handoff_artifact\": \"docs/json/opencode/secrets/rl-004-findings.v1.json\",\n  \"plan_artifact\": \"docs/json/opencode/plans/rl-004-secrets-policy.v1.json\"\n}","sent_at":"2026-05-30T11:53:31.291Z"}
