{"schema_version":"v1","message_id":"202605301153495_handoff","session_id":"ses_18748d10cffenCGpohMcaJapaL","sender":"lane-owner","recipient":"orchestrator","kind":"handoff","wave":null,"subject":"Lane RL-004 complete — Secrets Handling Policy Audit","body":"{\n  \"lane_id\": \"RL-004\",\n  \"status\": \"completed\",\n  \"waves_completed\": [\"learning\", \"plan\", \"review\", \"execution\", \"validation\"],\n  \"repair_cycles\": 0,\n  \"claims_verified\": 6,\n  \"files_created\": [\n    \"docs/json/opencode/secrets/rl-004-findings.v1.json\",\n    \"docs/json/opencode/plans/rl-004-secrets-policy.v1.json\",\n    \"docs/json/opencode/secrets/secrets-surface-map.v1.json\",\n    \"docs/json/opencode/secrets/secrets-surface-map-aggregated.v1.json\"\n  ],\n  \"files_modified\": [],\n  \"verification\": {\n    \"artifact_validated\": \"pass\"\n  },\n  \"blockers\": [],\n  \"findings_summary\": {\n    \"existing_redaction_mechanisms\": 8,\n    \"critical_security_gaps\": 5,\n    \"high_risk_secret_sites\": 18,\n    \"critical_risk_sites\": 3,\n    \"immediate_active_leak_fixes\": 2,\n    \"data_flow_categories\": [\"Provider API Keys\", \"OAuth Tokens\", \"Server Password\", \"GitHub OAuth\", \"Enterprise Storage Credentials\"]\n  },\n  \"top_findings\": [\n    \"sanitizedProcessEnv in packages/core/src/util/opencode-process.ts is a NO-OP — passes ALL env vars unchanged to subprocesses despite its name\",\n    \"createSidecarEnv in packages/desktop/src/main/server.ts:230 passes ALL env vars including server password to sidecar process without filtering\",\n    \"No encryption at rest: auth.json, mcp-auth.json, and SQLite account table store OAuth tokens in PLAINTEXT\",\n    \"Console cloud functions (packages/console/) log raw secrets — OAuth tokens, API keys, Stripe webhook payloads — to stdout\",\n    \"Enterprise storage reads AWS access keys/secret keys from process.env with non-null assertions\",\n    \"Multiple credential injection sites write secrets back into process.env (AWS_BEARER_TOKEN_BEDROCK, AICORE_SERVICE_KEY, OPENCODE_CONSOLE_TOKEN)\",\n    \"No ENV_BLOCKLIST, no file-read security, no bash command security, no general-purpose output scrubber exists anywhere\"\n  ],\n  \"critical_gaps\": [\n    \"GAP-A: sanitizedProcessEnv is a no-op — subprocess env passes ALL secrets\",\n    \"GAP-B: No file-read security — no binary detection, safe path, or sensitive file blocking\",\n    \"GAP-C: No bash command security — no rerouting, no dangerous pattern detection\",\n    \"GAP-D: No general-purpose output scrubber — tool output, agent messages, event payloads unprotected\",\n    \"GAP-E: No central ENV_BLOCKLIST utility exists\"\n  ],\n  \"existing_good_patterns\": [\n    \"GitHub OAuth tokens encrypted via Electron safeStorage (github-ipc.ts)\",\n    \"HTTP recorder redaction pipeline with 7 regex patterns (http-recorder/src/redaction.ts)\",\n    \"LLM provider error redaction (llm/src/route/executor.ts)\",\n    \"Debug packet config key-name redaction (opencode/src/debug/debug-packet.ts)\",\n    \"PG connection string sanitized in pool logging (opencode/src/storage/pg-pool.ts)\",\n    \"DuckDB SQL firewall blocks dangerous operations (opencode/src/storage/duckdb-firewall.ts)\",\n    \"Effect's Redacted type used in some paths (llm/src/route/auth.ts, database-config.ts)\"\n  ],\n  \"policy_layers_proposed\": [\n    \"Layer 1: Env-aware secret classifier (P0)\",\n    \"Layer 2: ENV_BLOCKLIST for subprocesses (P0)\",\n    \"Layer 3: Output sanitizer pipeline (P1)\",\n    \"Layer 4: File I/O protection (P1)\",\n    \"Layer 5: Credential lifecycle management (P2)\"\n  ],\n  \"lessons_learned\": [\n    \"No general-purpose secrets redaction exists in this codebase — always audit before assuming\",\n    \"Multiple sites write credentials into process.env as an anti-pattern — use SDK constructors or config injection instead\",\n    \"AGENTS.md describes Rig Relay security mechanisms (ENV_BLOCKLIST, sanitize_env_for_subprocess, etc.) that do NOT exist in this repo\",\n    \"The only encrypted-at-rest credential storage is Electron safeStorage for GitHub tokens — all other stores (SQLite, JSON files) are plaintext\",\n    \"Console cloud functions log raw secret values to stdout, which appears in production Cloudflare Worker logs\"\n  ],\n  \"recommendation\": \"merge\",\n  \"handoff_artifact\": \"docs/json/opencode/secrets/rl-004-findings.v1.json\",\n  \"plan_artifact\": \"docs/json/opencode/plans/rl-004-secrets-policy.v1.json\"\n}","sent_at":"2026-05-30T11:53:49.597Z"}
{"schema_version":"v1","message_id":"202605301154020_handoff","session_id":"ses_18748f603ffeBnAjmPjIKmOZpy","sender":"lane-owner","recipient":"orchestrator","kind":"handoff","wave":null,"subject":"Lane RL-001 complete — Safe/Degraded Mode Architecture Design","body":"{\n  \"lane_id\": \"RL-001\",\n  \"status\": \"completed\",\n  \"waves_completed\": [\"learning\", \"plan\", \"review\", \"execution\", \"validation\"],\n  \"repair_cycles\": 0,\n  \"claims_verified\": 8,\n  \"files_created\": [\"docs/json/opencode/plans/safe-degraded-mode-init.v1.json\"],\n  \"files_modified\": [],\n  \"verification\": { \"typecheck\": \"n/a (design only)\", \"tests\": \"n/a\" },\n  \"blockers\": [],\n  \"lessons\": [\n    \"The desktop app init flow has no degraded mode — sidecar failure shows crash dialog, not Safe Mode UI\",\n    \"PGlite init at packages/opencode/src/storage/db.pg.ts:31 has no try/catch — a corrupt data directory crashes the process\",\n    \"MCP.defaultLayer is an Effect.effect included in AppLayer.mergeAll() — a hanging MCP server blocks the entire app runtime\",\n    \"InitStep type has only 3 phases (server_waiting, sqlite_waiting, done) — needs extension for safe/degraded/repair phases\",\n    \"App already has wireWindowRecovery() with Relaunch/Export Logs/Quit dialog pattern to extend\"\n  ],\n  \"recommendation\": \"investigate\",\n  \"recommendation_detail\": \"Design artifact is complete. Recommend spawning an execution lane for Phase 1 (Init Flow Restructuring: main/index.ts, sidecar.ts, server.ts, preload/types.ts) and Phase 2 (Service Health Registry: new health.ts in opencode server). Phases 3-6 (UI, degraded indicators, session persistence, migration backup) can follow in subsequent lanes. Highest priority: wrap PGlite constructor in try/catch + add health reporting.\",\n  \"design_artifact\": \"docs/json/opencode/plans/safe-degraded-mode-init.v1.json\",\n  \"design_artifact_summary\": {\n    \"sections\": [\n      \"Executive Summary\",\n      \"Current Initialization Flow Map (12-step sequence with file:line refs)\",\n      \"9 Degradation Points Identified (critical/high/medium/low severities)\",\n      \"Proposed 3-Tier Architecture (Safe Mode → Degraded Mode → Full Mode)\",\n      \"6 Implementation Phases with per-file change descriptions\",\n      \"6 Architecture Decision Records (ADRs)\",\n      \"7 Risks Assessed with mitigations\",\n      \"Claims Calibration (8 verified, 4 unverified)\",\n      \"Files Summary (~17 new files, ~18 modified files, ~2,500 estimated new lines)\"\n    ],\n    \"key_design_decisions\": [\n      \"Safe Mode runs in same renderer process (no separate window)\",\n      \"Health registry is an Effect Service reported via /global/health\",\n      \"Safe mode diagnosis uses static HTML/JS (no server needed)\",\n      \"InitStep extended with detailed error phases\",\n      \"Plugin quarantine uses persistent crash counters in config\",\n      \"Sidecar communicates component status via typed IPC messages\"\n    ]\n  }\n}","sent_at":"2026-05-30T11:54:02.061Z"}
